Template: mailman3-core/config_hyperkitty
Type: boolean
_Description: Should DebConf add HyperKitty config to mailman.cfg?
 Mailman3 comes usually with HyperKitty as an archiver for its
 Mailing lists traffic. This implies adding some configuration
 into /etc/mailman3/mailman.cfg file.
 .
 Select "Yes" if you wish to have these configurations installed
 into the mailman.cfg file right now.
 .
 You can also extract the configurations from the file
 hyperkitty_additionnal.cfg located in
 /usr/share/mailman3/mailman3-core_hyperkitty-snippet.cfg.
